<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                            <head>No. 479.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peixotto</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 12, 1872</date>. (Received March
                                    12.)</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The consul of Germany has called to
                                inform me that he last evening received a telegram from Prince
                                Bismarck, instructing him to sign the note addressed to the
                                Roumanian government concerning the persecution of the. Israelites,
                                copy of which I had the honor to inclose and refer to in my dispatch
                                No. 21, of the 9th instant.</p>
                            <p>* * * * * *</p>
                            <p>I am, &amp;c., &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>BENJ. F. PEIXOTTO,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Consul.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>